In [6]:
# Loop through each class folder
for class_index, class_name in enumerate(classes):
    image_folder = os.path.join(dataset_folder, class_name, 'images')
    mask_folder = os.path.join(dataset_folder, class_name, 'lung masks')

    # Loop through each file in the image folder
    for filename in os.listdir(image_folder):
        image_path = os.path.join(image_folder, filename)
        mask_path = os.path.join(mask_folder, filename)

        # Load images and masks
        img = cv2.imread(image_path, cv2.IMREAD_GRAYSCALE).astype(np.uint8)
        mask = cv2.imread(mask_path, cv2.IMREAD_GRAYSCALE).astype(np.uint8)

        # Resize images and masks to target size
        img = cv2.resize(img, target_size)
        mask = cv2.resize(mask, target_size)

        # Apply intensity thresholding
        _, img_threshold = cv2.threshold(img, 0, 255, cv2.THRESH_BINARY | cv2.THRESH_OTSU)
        
        
        # Apply histogram equalization
        img_equalized = cv2.equalizeHist(img)
        
        # Apply Gaussian blur
        img_blurred = cv2.GaussianBlur(img, (5, 5), 0)

        # Append preprocessed images, masks, and labels to the lists
        preprocessed_images.extend([img_threshold, img_equalized, img_blurred])
        preprocessed_masks.extend([mask] * 3)
        labels.extend([class_index] * 3)  # Assign label index for each image

# Convert lists to numpy arrays
preprocessed_images = np.array(preprocessed_images)
preprocessed_masks = np.array(preprocessed_masks)
labels = np.array(labels)

from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split

# Split the combined data into training and temporary data (80% training, 20% temporary)
train_data, temp_data = train_test_split(combined_data, test_size=0.2, random_state=42)

# Split the temporary data into validation and test sets (50% validation, 50% test)
val_data, test_data = train_test_split(temp_data, test_size=0.5, random_state=42)

from keras.preprocessing.image import ImageDataGenerator

# Define ImageDataGenerator for image augmentation
datagen = ImageDataGenerator(
    rotation_range=20,
    width_shift_range=0.1,
    height_shift_range=0.1,
    shear_range=0.2,
    zoom_range=0.2,
    horizontal_flip=True,
    fill_mode='nearest')

# Fit the ImageDataGenerator on preprocessed images
datagen.fit(preprocessed_images)

# Apply image augmentation to preprocessed images and masks
augmented_images = []
augmented_masks = []

for i in range(len(preprocessed_images)):
    for X_batch, mask_batch in datagen.flow(preprocessed_images[[i]], preprocessed_masks[[i]], batch_size=1):
        augmented_images.append(X_batch[0])
        augmented_masks.append(mask_batch[0])
        break

# Convert augmented data to numpy arrays
augmented_images = np.array(augmented_images)
augmented_masks = np.array(augmented_masks)

# Print the sizes of the augmented data
print("Augmented data size:", augmented_images.shape)
print("Augmented mask size:", augmented_masks.shape)

Augmented data size: (16251, 224, 224, 1)

In [23]:
import tensorflow as tf
from tensorflow.keras.models import Model
from tensorflow.keras.layers import Input, Conv2D, MaxPooling2D, Flatten, Dense, concatenate

# Assuming the shape of your images and masks
input_shape = (224, 224, 1)

# Input layers
image_input = Input(shape=input_shape, name='image_input')
mask_input = Input(shape=input_shape, name='mask_input')

# Convolutional layers for images
conv1_image = Conv2D(32, (3, 3), activation='relu', padding='same')(image_input)
maxpool_image = MaxPooling2D((2, 2))(conv1_image)
conv2_image = Conv2D(64, (3, 3), activation='relu', padding='same')(maxpool_image)
maxpool_image = MaxPooling2D((2, 2))(conv2_image)
flatten_image = Flatten()(maxpool_image)

# Convolutional layers for masks
conv1_mask = Conv2D(32, (3, 3), activation='relu', padding='same')(mask_input)
maxpool_mask = MaxPooling2D((2, 2))(conv1_mask)
conv2_mask = Conv2D(64, (3, 3), activation='relu', padding='same')(maxpool_mask)
maxpool_mask = MaxPooling2D((2, 2))(conv2_mask)
flatten_mask = Flatten()(maxpool_mask)

# Concatenate flattened image and mask features
concatenated_features = concatenate([flatten_image, flatten_mask])

# Fully connected layers
fc1 = Dense(128, activation='relu')(concatenated_features)
output = Dense(3, activation='softmax', name='output')(fc1)

# Create the model
model = Model(inputs=[image_input, mask_input], outputs=output)

# Compile the model (you can choose an appropriate optimizer and loss function)
model.compile(optimizer='adam', loss='categorical_crossentropy', metrics=['accuracy'])

# Display the summary of the model architecture
model.summary()
